## Description
The **On-Demand HTTP Ingress&nbsp;**resource allows to trigger the execution of an On-Demand workflow via API.

> Note

Both native and retro-compatibility modes are supported for the Request. The Response is an XML file.

For more information on API integration, see: [Web Services Exposed by On-Demand Workflows](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/DD/Web+Services+Exposed+by+On-Demand+Workflows).

## Additional creation parameters
None.&nbsp;

## Resource editor
None.

## Deploy parameters
![](data:image/png;base64,)

Section

Field

Description

**Configuration**

**Tenant**

Select the&nbsp;**Tenant** on which you want to deploy the resource from the drop-down menu.

**Workflow**

**Resource**

Select the On-Demand Workflow resource that will be triggered when calling this endpoint.

> Important

If the selected workflow has not been deployed on the selected tenant, a warning message is displayed.

**Endpoint**

**Path**

Enter the final part of the URL path to call.

> Note

The custom path may include "/" characters within (e.g. **custompath** or **custompath/subpath**)

For example: "po-demo/2023-10";  the resulting URL will be: [*https://{prefix}-qa-aws-frnk-1-doxee-int.cloud.doxee.com*](https://da-qa-aws-frnk-1-doxee-int.cloud.doxee.com)*/****po-demo/2023-10****/process*

**Keys**

Select the [Ingress Credentials](/doxee-platform/docs/ingress-credentials-resource-reference) resource(s) to use for API authentication.

> Note

Up to 10 API keys can be used at the same time to avoid expiration issues.

**Parallel requests**

Select the maximum number of allowed requests per second. The available options are:

- 5&nbsp;*(default)*

- 15

- 30

- 60

- 90

> Important

If the selected rate limit doesn't include autoscaling, a warning message is displayed. In this case, it's necessary to adjust the capacity manually.

> Tip

Click **Publish** to publish the release on the tenant.

Click **Deploy** to publish and enable the release on the tenant.
